1
00:00:06,016 --> 00:00:07,744
(1996)

2
00:00:07,744 --> 00:00:09,823
I heard their connections
are extremely powerful.

3
00:00:10,304 --> 00:00:12,464
It may look
like an entertainment complex.

4
00:00:12,743 --> 00:00:13,944
But in reality,

5
00:00:16,583 --> 00:00:18,343
it's an unofficial Personnel Bureau.

6
00:00:18,663 --> 00:00:20,144
Personnel Bureau?

7
00:00:20,903 --> 00:00:21,984
That extreme?

8
00:00:22,784 --> 00:00:23,663
Look at you.

9
00:00:23,823 --> 00:00:24,744
Just like me,

10
00:00:24,823 --> 00:00:26,023
showing your inexperience.

11
00:00:26,904 --> 00:00:28,464
Look like you've never seen the world.

12
00:00:35,503 --> 00:00:36,223
So

13
00:00:36,464 --> 00:00:37,624
you apply for a job here

14
00:00:38,023 --> 00:00:39,224
to broaden your horizons?

15
00:00:40,904 --> 00:00:41,904
Not entirely.

16
00:00:42,504 --> 00:00:43,783
Mainly

17
00:00:44,343 --> 00:00:45,343
to make money.

18
00:00:45,632 --> 00:00:47,504
Jeez. So blunt?

19
00:00:48,383 --> 00:00:49,504
What's wrong with it?

20
00:00:49,944 --> 00:00:51,184
Don't you want money?

21
00:00:51,944 --> 00:00:52,944
Without money,

22
00:00:53,383 --> 00:00:54,504
how to make your waiters

23
00:00:54,504 --> 00:00:55,703
wait on you hand and foot?

24
00:00:55,904 --> 00:00:57,504
How do you become a VIP here?

25
00:00:59,904 --> 00:01:00,904
That makes sense.

26
00:01:02,023 --> 00:01:03,063
It makes sense, right?

27
00:01:04,743 --> 00:01:05,743
Stick with me.

28
00:01:05,984 --> 00:01:07,023
I'm really sharp.

29
00:01:10,863 --> 00:01:11,363
Okay.

30
00:01:11,583 --> 00:01:12,423
I'll stick with you

31
00:01:12,624 --> 00:01:13,264
from now on.

32
00:01:20,984 --> 00:01:22,464
I was only gone for a short while,

33
00:01:22,783 --> 00:01:24,143
and you've picked up a man.

34
00:01:24,904 --> 00:01:25,583
Ruoxi,

35
00:01:25,984 --> 00:01:26,904
introduce us.

36
00:01:27,024 --> 00:01:27,703
Who is this?

37
00:01:28,824 --> 00:01:30,104
This is...

38
00:01:32,863 --> 00:01:33,664
This gentleman is...

39
00:01:33,664 --> 00:01:34,783
Mr. Tu, your cigarettes.

40
00:01:37,384 --> 00:01:38,184
Mr. Tu?

41
00:01:39,464 --> 00:01:40,063
You're Mr. Tu,

42
00:01:40,063 --> 00:01:40,783
Tu Jiasheng?

43
00:01:41,824 --> 00:01:42,384
Ruoxi,

44
00:01:42,583 --> 00:01:43,303
get up.

45
00:01:43,744 --> 00:01:44,744
Get up!

46
00:01:45,503 --> 00:01:46,503
This is our boss.

47
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:50,824
Your cigarette.

48
00:02:00,876 --> 00:02:02,974
=The Glory Fades=

49
00:02:03,424 --> 00:02:05,792
=Episode 9=
(The Gambit)

50
00:02:16,463 --> 00:02:17,064
See?

51
00:02:17,984 --> 00:02:19,463
You two sisters look so alike.

52
00:02:20,384 --> 00:02:21,784
I'm not the only one who noticed.

53
00:02:22,984 --> 00:02:24,384
People who know you see it too.

54
00:02:28,264 --> 00:02:28,824
Why does

55
00:02:28,824 --> 00:02:30,463
Su Yunian come to work here?

56
00:02:31,183 --> 00:02:31,863
I think

57
00:02:33,023 --> 00:02:34,384
we both know very well.

58
00:03:02,583 --> 00:03:04,064
I won't drag her into this

59
00:03:04,583 --> 00:03:05,623
or let anything harm her.

60
00:03:15,023 --> 00:03:15,824
Ruoxi,

61
00:03:17,544 --> 00:03:18,463
this time,

62
00:03:21,183 --> 00:03:22,344
I'm going to gamble.

63
00:03:39,863 --> 00:03:41,224
It's me.

64
00:03:41,984 --> 00:03:42,824
Ruxue,

65
00:03:42,824 --> 00:03:43,944
what are you doing here?

66
00:03:43,944 --> 00:03:45,064
You scared me!

67
00:03:46,344 --> 00:03:47,504
You're criticizing me?

68
00:03:47,504 --> 00:03:48,703
I came to use the bathroom.

69
00:03:48,703 --> 00:03:50,064
You're acting like a spy.

70
00:03:50,264 --> 00:03:51,303
What are you doing here?

71
00:03:52,984 --> 00:03:54,264
Gazing through the door,

72
00:03:54,504 --> 00:03:55,423
pining for Mr. Tu.

73
00:03:55,423 --> 00:03:56,224
Right?

74
00:03:56,703 --> 00:03:57,423
Hey,

75
00:03:57,544 --> 00:03:58,583
stop teasing me.

76
00:04:00,984 --> 00:04:02,583
I know

77
00:04:02,583 --> 00:04:03,944
you like him.

78
00:04:04,863 --> 00:04:06,863
You started on the same day as Ruoxi,

79
00:04:06,863 --> 00:04:08,664
and met Mr. Tu on the same day.

80
00:04:08,784 --> 00:04:10,224
Not even ten minutes apart.

81
00:04:10,423 --> 00:04:11,023
Right?

82
00:04:11,224 --> 00:04:12,143
Yeah.

83
00:04:12,303 --> 00:04:13,183
Just ten minutes.

84
00:04:13,824 --> 00:04:16,023
Yet she got ahead of me.

85
00:04:17,423 --> 00:04:18,863
Maybe that's just fate.

86
00:04:19,544 --> 00:04:21,544
Mr. Tu barely glances at me,

87
00:04:22,063 --> 00:04:24,024
while he always

88
00:04:24,423 --> 00:04:26,144
protects Su Yunian.

89
00:04:27,063 --> 00:04:28,063
What a pity.

90
00:04:28,383 --> 00:04:29,224
I don't have

91
00:04:29,224 --> 00:04:30,784
the eyes and brows like An Ruoxi's.

92
00:04:32,584 --> 00:04:34,303
Look at you.

93
00:04:34,344 --> 00:04:36,303
You really think
it's just about the face?

94
00:04:40,904 --> 00:04:41,743
Ruoxi

95
00:04:41,863 --> 00:04:44,024
won with the details.

96
00:04:44,104 --> 00:04:45,383
She took care of Mr. Tu

97
00:04:45,383 --> 00:04:47,224
extremely meticulously.

98
00:04:48,784 --> 00:04:50,063
I know that.

99
00:04:50,423 --> 00:04:51,704
She told me.

100
00:04:53,224 --> 00:04:54,664
(And because of that,)

101
00:04:54,943 --> 00:04:56,183
he fell in love with you?

102
00:04:57,623 --> 00:04:58,183
Come on.

103
00:04:58,623 --> 00:04:59,623
Tell the truth.

104
00:05:00,904 --> 00:05:01,743
That day

105
00:05:01,823 --> 00:05:02,984
when Mr. Zhao assigned you

106
00:05:02,984 --> 00:05:04,423
to take him back to his room.

107
00:05:05,344 --> 00:05:06,544
What else did you do to him?

108
00:05:07,584 --> 00:05:08,664
What did I do?

109
00:05:09,904 --> 00:05:11,383
What could I even do?

110
00:05:11,584 --> 00:05:13,104
He was completely drunk.

111
00:05:13,904 --> 00:05:16,423
(Mr. Zhao and I helped him into bed.)

112
00:05:16,943 --> 00:05:18,183
(Mr. Zhao returned to Room 888)

113
00:05:18,183 --> 00:05:19,360
(to accompany Director Zhao.)

114
00:05:19,704 --> 00:05:21,224
(I took his shoes off)

115
00:05:21,544 --> 00:05:22,943
to make him more comfortable.

116
00:05:23,464 --> 00:05:24,144
Then what?

117
00:05:25,303 --> 00:05:26,344
Then

118
00:05:26,984 --> 00:05:28,423
(I turned off the TV.)

119
00:05:30,024 --> 00:05:30,823
Go on.

120
00:05:31,224 --> 00:05:32,423
Then I set the AC

121
00:05:32,423 --> 00:05:33,623
to 26 degrees.

122
00:05:34,263 --> 00:05:36,183
Thought that'd be
more comfortable for him.

123
00:05:37,904 --> 00:05:38,623
That's all?

124
00:05:41,303 --> 00:05:43,224
I worried he'd be thirsty
from all the drinking,

125
00:05:43,423 --> 00:05:44,464
(so I left a cup)

126
00:05:44,464 --> 00:05:46,024
(of sober-up water by his bed.)

127
00:05:47,024 --> 00:05:48,464
Also,

128
00:05:48,743 --> 00:05:50,584
(I turned off his bedside lamp.)

129
00:05:50,623 --> 00:05:51,664
(Finally,)

130
00:05:52,263 --> 00:05:53,943
(I bagged the instant noodle cup)

131
00:05:54,024 --> 00:05:55,423
(he'd finished in a trash bag)

132
00:05:55,704 --> 00:05:57,063
(and tossed it in the bin.)

133
00:05:57,823 --> 00:05:58,743
That's everything.

134
00:06:02,623 --> 00:06:03,704
I get it now.

135
00:06:04,544 --> 00:06:05,544
It's the details.

136
00:06:08,144 --> 00:06:09,224
Oh, Yunyan.

137
00:06:09,704 --> 00:06:11,183
You're absolutely adorable.

138
00:06:12,584 --> 00:06:13,623
Ruxue,

139
00:06:14,144 --> 00:06:15,503
what exactly do you mean?

140
00:06:17,024 --> 00:06:18,344
What else do you actually know?

141
00:06:18,423 --> 00:06:19,303
Tell me.

142
00:06:20,383 --> 00:06:21,904
How would I know?

143
00:06:22,383 --> 00:06:24,063
But Ruoxi definitely had secrets.

144
00:06:25,263 --> 00:06:26,584
You think treating her to a meal

145
00:06:26,584 --> 00:06:27,303
or some drinks

146
00:06:27,423 --> 00:06:28,904
would make her spill everything?

147
00:06:29,503 --> 00:06:31,984
Who'd willingly give their man away?

148
00:06:32,303 --> 00:06:33,784
Do you agree?

149
00:06:34,544 --> 00:06:35,623
I knew

150
00:06:35,943 --> 00:06:37,464
it couldn't be that simple.

151
00:06:38,823 --> 00:06:40,344
But she's already dead.

152
00:06:40,344 --> 00:06:41,423
Where can I even ask?

153
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:42,984
Not necessarily.

154
00:06:43,464 --> 00:06:44,664
Ms. Bai mentioned

155
00:06:44,823 --> 00:06:46,263
An Ruoxi kept a diary.

156
00:06:46,423 --> 00:06:47,544
She wrote down

157
00:06:47,544 --> 00:06:48,464
all the secrets.

158
00:06:48,464 --> 00:06:49,263
Secrets?

159
00:06:49,544 --> 00:06:50,383
What kind of secrets?

160
00:06:51,123 --> 00:06:51,623
Silly.

161
00:06:51,623 --> 00:06:52,904
Secrets to manage her man.

162
00:06:52,984 --> 00:06:54,544
All about what Mr. Tu liked.

163
00:06:54,544 --> 00:06:55,144
Everything.

164
00:06:55,284 --> 00:06:55,784
Well.

165
00:06:55,784 --> 00:06:56,544
That, um.

166
00:06:56,904 --> 00:06:58,183
Must I spell it out?

167
00:06:59,063 --> 00:07:00,584
But I can't find it.

168
00:07:02,104 --> 00:07:02,863
Word is

169
00:07:03,024 --> 00:07:04,464
it's in Room 999.

170
00:07:07,423 --> 00:07:08,503
I just remembered.

171
00:07:08,584 --> 00:07:09,863
I'm meeting Director Jamil.

172
00:07:09,984 --> 00:07:10,943
He's waiting for me.

173
00:07:11,183 --> 00:07:11,943
I have to go now.

174
00:07:11,943 --> 00:07:12,443
Yunyan.

175
00:07:12,503 --> 00:07:13,063
Ruxue.

176
00:07:13,323 --> 00:07:15,063
- I'm heading out now.
- Ruxue.

177
00:07:16,943 --> 00:07:17,784
Ruxue.

178
00:07:49,024 --> 00:07:49,704
You're drunk.

179
00:07:55,303 --> 00:07:56,183
No one's stealing it.

180
00:07:56,183 --> 00:07:56,984
Give it to me.

181
00:08:32,823 --> 00:08:33,743
It's still early.

182
00:08:33,743 --> 00:08:34,584
Go sleep upstairs.

183
00:08:43,464 --> 00:08:44,184
Thanks,

184
00:08:44,184 --> 00:08:44,863
Lu.

185
00:08:49,187 --> 00:08:52,352
(Deep In The Bustle Security:
Captain Liu, Wang)

186
00:08:56,743 --> 00:08:57,623
Keep a close watch.

187
00:08:58,623 --> 00:08:59,503
I'm off

188
00:09:00,464 --> 00:09:01,503
to unwind a bit.

189
00:09:29,543 --> 00:09:30,984
(An Ruoxi kept a diary.)

190
00:09:31,143 --> 00:09:32,064
(She wrote down)

191
00:09:32,064 --> 00:09:33,184
(all the secrets.)

192
00:09:34,584 --> 00:09:37,503
(Word is it's in Room 999.)

193
00:09:45,783 --> 00:09:46,304
Ms. Bai,

194
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:48,104
here's my monthly work summary.

195
00:09:48,424 --> 00:09:49,663
Videos and photos

196
00:09:49,824 --> 00:09:50,704
are already prepared.

197
00:09:51,064 --> 00:09:51,663
Good.

198
00:09:52,184 --> 00:09:53,424
Any important figures?

199
00:09:57,623 --> 00:09:59,023
A special envoy from the Cabinet.

200
00:10:06,263 --> 00:10:06,944
Good.

201
00:10:07,464 --> 00:10:08,783
I'll save it in Room 999 later.

202
00:10:09,503 --> 00:10:10,344
Attend to your tasks.

203
00:10:10,623 --> 00:10:11,224
Okay.

204
00:10:50,424 --> 00:10:50,984
Hello.

205
00:10:51,464 --> 00:10:52,543
Manni, in the office?

206
00:10:54,023 --> 00:10:54,663
Talk in person.

207
00:11:26,424 --> 00:11:27,104
Does it hurt?

208
00:11:29,064 --> 00:11:29,564
No.

209
00:11:31,543 --> 00:11:32,944
It's just a slap.

210
00:11:35,584 --> 00:11:36,224
No big deal.

211
00:11:47,064 --> 00:11:47,863
In the future,

212
00:11:48,503 --> 00:11:49,104
there will be

213
00:11:49,104 --> 00:11:50,783
tricks harsher than a slap.

214
00:11:52,944 --> 00:11:53,663
But

215
00:11:54,383 --> 00:11:55,424
I just don't believe

216
00:11:56,584 --> 00:11:58,424
that scapegoat did it.

217
00:12:31,344 --> 00:12:33,584
(This is the second floor of Room 999.)

218
00:12:34,304 --> 00:12:36,104
(So big and luxurious.)

219
00:12:37,984 --> 00:12:40,344
(Oh An Ruoxi,)

220
00:12:40,424 --> 00:12:42,383
(you really had great fortune.)

221
00:12:43,304 --> 00:12:44,184
(What a pity.)

222
00:12:44,464 --> 00:12:45,623
(Your life was short.)

223
00:12:47,663 --> 00:12:49,944
(Mr. Tu's bedroom)

224
00:12:50,344 --> 00:12:52,104
(must be that one.)

225
00:13:21,184 --> 00:13:22,623
(Mr. Tu sleeps)

226
00:13:22,623 --> 00:13:24,023
(without wearing any clothes?)

227
00:13:25,464 --> 00:13:27,023
(What a perfect opportunity!)

228
00:13:27,023 --> 00:13:28,903
(And I caught it.)

229
00:14:00,023 --> 00:14:00,863
(No.)

230
00:14:01,383 --> 00:14:02,663
(Since I'm already here,)

231
00:14:03,584 --> 00:14:05,584
(I should try to seize the opportunity.)

232
00:14:06,263 --> 00:14:07,503
(Then)

233
00:14:07,984 --> 00:14:09,383
(I turned off the TV.)

234
00:14:09,383 --> 00:14:10,984
(Yes, turn off the TV.)

235
00:14:22,143 --> 00:14:23,424
(What else?)

236
00:14:24,743 --> 00:14:25,623
(Instant noodles.)

237
00:14:25,783 --> 00:14:27,503
(I bagged the instant noodle cup)

238
00:14:27,503 --> 00:14:28,903
(he'd finished in a trash bag)

239
00:14:29,184 --> 00:14:30,623
(and tossed it in the bin.)

240
00:14:32,344 --> 00:14:33,984
(What else?)

241
00:14:34,863 --> 00:14:36,824
(I worried he'd be thirsty
from all the drinking,)

242
00:14:37,023 --> 00:14:37,984
(so I left a cup)

243
00:14:37,984 --> 00:14:39,663
(of sober-up water by his bed.)

244
00:14:40,224 --> 00:14:41,503
(Sober-up water.)

245
00:14:41,783 --> 00:14:43,503
(Should be honey water.)

246
00:15:04,263 --> 00:15:06,383
(Yes, and the AC temperature.)

247
00:15:06,824 --> 00:15:08,743
(I set the AC to 26 degrees.)

248
00:15:09,064 --> 00:15:11,263
(Thought that'd be
more comfortable for him.)

249
00:15:16,584 --> 00:15:18,584
(It's basically a perfect recreation.)

250
00:15:18,903 --> 00:15:20,743
(I turned off his bedside lamp.)

251
00:15:20,743 --> 00:15:23,064
(Yes, and the bedside lamp.)

252
00:15:25,944 --> 00:15:27,424
(That should be about it now.)

253
00:15:29,304 --> 00:15:30,464
(Unfortunately,)

254
00:15:31,224 --> 00:15:32,663
(I still can't...)

255
00:15:33,984 --> 00:15:34,704
(It's fine.)

256
00:15:35,383 --> 00:15:36,543
(There's still time.)

257
00:15:51,344 --> 00:15:53,663
(Better days will come eventually.)

258
00:15:54,184 --> 00:15:55,984
(After all, I've seen)

259
00:15:56,224 --> 00:15:58,304
(the second floor of Room 999.)

260
00:16:12,544 --> 00:16:13,783
(No.)

261
00:16:14,224 --> 00:16:15,424
(What about the diary?)

262
00:16:23,944 --> 00:16:25,663
(So the first floor of Room 999)

263
00:16:25,824 --> 00:16:27,584
(is the archive room.)

264
00:16:28,424 --> 00:16:29,783
(That means)

265
00:16:30,143 --> 00:16:32,503
(the guest info we usually collect)

266
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:34,344
(all gets compiled here.)

267
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:39,456
(Deep In The Bustle Historical
Transaction Ledger)

268
00:16:40,896 --> 00:16:42,304
(Expense List)

269
00:16:43,984 --> 00:16:44,903
(No wonder)

270
00:16:45,704 --> 00:16:48,023
(so many people
are tightly controlled by them.)

271
00:16:49,584 --> 00:16:50,304
(Forget it.)

272
00:16:50,984 --> 00:16:52,143
(The diary can't be here.)

273
00:17:06,263 --> 00:17:07,584
(An Ruoxi,)

274
00:17:09,143 --> 00:17:09,984
(so long.)

275
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:20,794
♪If the heart can't hear the sorrow♪

276
00:17:21,093 --> 00:17:24,284
♪It only makes everything look so fake♪

277
00:17:26,016 --> 00:17:29,737
♪Your eyes resemble hers too much♪

278
00:17:30,286 --> 00:17:33,085
♪Who makes me forget whom♪

279
00:17:34,556 --> 00:17:38,286
♪The warmth in my heart is fading♪

280
00:17:38,510 --> 00:17:42,007
♪Every glance feels like atonement♪

281
00:17:43,406 --> 00:17:47,093
♪Ambiguity hidden in the night breeze♪

282
00:17:47,731 --> 00:17:52,846
♪Blows away the chance to explain♪

283
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:57,684
♪I feel guilty♪

284
00:17:58,144 --> 00:18:01,998
♪I'll have no regrets
even I leave quietly♪

285
00:18:02,862 --> 00:18:06,305
♪Even in tears♪

286
00:18:07,054 --> 00:18:10,968
♪It doesn't matter♪

287
00:18:11,150 --> 00:18:14,973
